race.comment: CANYA ERUPT (7) is a progressive type who recorded his 4th career win last time out (33.81) at Sandown. The form from his last run stacks up well. In top form and looks a key chance again. FADE TO BLACK (4) has a strong record this trip with five wins and three placings from 10 starts. Recorded a one length win (34.61) in a Grade 4/5 last time at The Meadows. Looks suited here and can measure up. PAW GRADY (1) turned in a plain run last time when fifth at Bendigo over 660m behind Panama Rhode (38.40) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at his previous run. One of the better hopes. ENGELKE ROAD (8) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when fourth (36.97), beaten 3.5 lengths. Form from his last run is proving to be solid.
